@startuml bff-architecture
!include <C4/C4_Component>
!include <logos/vue>
!include <logos/laravel>
!include <logos/redis>

title BFF Architecture - Laravel Backend for Frontend

LAYOUT_TOP_DOWN()

Container_Boundary(browser, "Browser (Vue SPA)") {
    Component(dashboard_vue, "Pages/Dashboard.vue", "Vue Component", "• Receives props from Inertia\n• Displays aggregated data\n• No direct API calls", $sprite="vue")
}

Rel_Down(dashboard_vue, inertia, "Inertia.js (HTTP)", "")

Container_Boundary(laravel_bff, "Laravel BFF Layer (PHP 8.2)") {
    Component(controller, "Controllers/DashboardController.php", "Laravel Controller", "• Receives HTTP request\n• Calls ExternalApiService\n• Aggregates data from multiple APIs\n• Transforms data for UI\n• Returns Inertia response", $sprite="laravel")

    Component(service, "Services/ExternalApiService.php", "Service Layer", "• Makes HTTP calls to external APIs\n• Implements caching (Redis)\n• Retry logic & error handling\n• Parallel request support\n• Data transformation", $sprite="laravel")
}

Rel_Down(inertia, controller, "", "")
Rel_Down(controller, service, "", "")

Container_Boundary(external_apis, "External APIs") {
    System_Ext(api1, "External API #1", "(Users)")
    System_Ext(api2, "External API #2", "(Orders)")
    System_Ext(api3, "External API #3", "(Analytics)")
}

Rel_Down(service, api1, "", "")
Rel_Down(service, api2, "", "")
Rel_Down(service, api3, "", "")

note right of dashboard_vue
  **Vue Component**
  Single Page Application
  Material Design 3 (Vuetify)

  No API logic - just presentation
end note

note right of controller
  **Request Handler**
  Orchestrates data fetching
  Aggregates multiple API responses
  Transforms data for frontend

  Example:
  public function dashboard() {
    $users = $this->service->getUsers();
    $orders = $this->service->getOrders();
    return Inertia::render('Dashboard', [
      'users' => $users,
      'orders' => $orders
    ]);
  }
end note

note right of service
  **API Aggregation Layer**
  • Redis caching (5 min TTL)
  • Retry policy (3 attempts)
  • Circuit breaker pattern
  • Parallel requests (Promise::all)
  • Error fallbacks

  Benefits:
  ✓ Single point of API integration
  ✓ Centralized error handling
  ✓ Consistent caching strategy
  ✓ Easy testing & mocking
end note

@enduml
